          <div class="pricing-card__note">Waived when you proceed with the repair</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section class="wh-faq">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Questions Woodland Hills Customers Ask</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Do you offer same-day appliance repair in Woodland Hills, CA?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. Our technicians cover all of Woodland Hills — Walnut Acres, Girard Tract, College Acres, Carlson Park, Vista De Oro, and all of 91364 and 91367. Call before noon for same-day afternoon service.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Does Woodland Hills' hot Valley climate affect appliances?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. 100°F+ summer days put refrigerator compressors under significant load and accelerate condenser coil dust buildup. We include a coil inspection on every Woodland Hills refrigerator call and recommend annual pre-summer cleaning each May.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Does LADWP hard water affect appliances in Woodland Hills?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. LADWP runs 230–310 mg/L throughout 91364 and 91367. Ice maker inlet valves and dishwasher spray arms scale faster here. We check proactively on every relevant call.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Are you available on weekends in Woodland Hills?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. Saturday 8am–7pm and Sunday 9am–5pm.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What appliance brands do you repair in Woodland Hills?</summary><div class="faq-answer">All major brands: Samsung, LG, GE, Whirlpool, KitchenAid, Bosch, Maytag, Sub-Zero, Wolf, Thermador, and more. OEM parts on every vehicle.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">What is your diagnostic fee in Woodland Hills?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Our diagnostic fee is $89, waived when you proceed with the repair. Written estimate before we start. Most Woodland Hills repairs run $150–$400.</div></details>
        <details class="faq-item"><summary class="faq-question">Do you also serve Calabasas, West Hills, and Tarzana?</summary><div class="faq-answer">Yes. Our Woodland Hills service extends to Calabasas, West Hills, Tarzana, Canoga Park, Chatsworth, and all of the western San Fernando Valley.</div></details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- NEARBY -->
